        <para id="id1167935073904">Next, we turn our attention to eliminating the (-3) term in row 3. We can do so by multiplying each term of row 2 by (-3) and subtracting the results from the corresponding terms in row 3. This produces the matrix</para>
        <equation id="id1167912960209">
          <m:math>
            <m:semantics>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mfenced open="(" close=")">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mtable>
                          <m:mtr>
                            <m:mtd>
                              <m:mrow>
                                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                                <m:mrow/>
                              </m:mrow>
                            </m:mtd>
                            <m:mtd>
                              <m:mrow>
                                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                                <m:mrow/>
                              </m:mrow>
                            </m:mtd>
                            <m:mtd>
                              <m:mrow>
                                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                                <m:mrow/>
                              </m:mrow>
                            </m:mtd>
                          </m:mtr>
                          <m:mtr>
                            <m:mtd>
                              <m:mrow>
                                <m:mn>0</m:mn>
                                <m:mrow/>
